{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Krun Macula<ref>"Krun Regio" in some early maps</ref> |image = [[File:Pluto-BrassKnuckles-20150716.jpg|frameless|250px]] |caption = The [[Brass Knuckles (Pluto)|Brass Knuckles]] chain of equatorial dark regions on [[Pluto]] |location = [[Pluto]] |coordinates= {{coord|15|S|150|W|globe:pluto_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |peak = |discoverer = |eponym = [[Krun]] }}
'''Krun''' is the westernmost of the "[[Brass Knuckles (Pluto)|Brass Knuckles]]", a series of equatorial dark regions on [[Pluto]]. It is named after [[Krun]]<!-- {{IPA-mid|kʰrʌn|}} - might be [u], checking with native speakers-->, the greatest of the five [[Mandaeism|Mandaean]] lords of the underworld.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chang|first1=Kenneth|title=NASA’s New Horizons Spacecraft Completes Flyby of Pluto|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/15/science/space/nasa-new-horizons-spacecraft-reaches-pluto.html|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=14 July 2015|date=14 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rogers|first1=Adam|title=The New, Nerdy Mythology of Pluto's Place Names|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/07/new-nerdy-mythology-plutos-place-names/|publisher=Wired|accessdate=14 July 2015|date=14 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Mandaeans on Pluto|url = http://www.ancienthistorymagazine.com/pw/ancient-history-magazine/blog/mandaeans-on-pluto/|website = Ancient History Magazine|accessdate = 2015-07-23|last = Lendering|first = Jona}}</ref> [[File:PIA20037-Pluto-NewHorizons-20150713.jpg|thumb|center|250px|<center>Krun Macula - context</center>]] [[File:Krun on Pluto.jpg|thumb|Krun is the dark region at center. It is southeast of the eastern lobe of the bright heart-shaped [[Tombaugh Regio]].]] Krun is the third largest equatorial dark region on Pluto, after Cthulhu and Balrog. It extends nearly to 180 degrees longitude, the Plutonian longitude opposite Charon.
