{{South Korea national parks}}
'''Mudeungsan National Park''', previously '''Mudeungsan Provincial Park''', is located in the city of [[Gwangju]] and the province of [[Jeollanam-do]], [[South Korea]].<ref>[http://english.visitkorea.or.kr/enu/SI/SI_EN_3_1_1_1.jsp?cid=264347 Mudeungsan National Park (무등산국립공원)]. ''VISITKorea''. Retrieved 20 March 2015.</ref> The park was designated a [[provincial park]] on 22 May 1972 and was upgraded to [[national park]] status in 2012, making it South Korea's 21st national park. The park has an area of {{convert|75.45|km2|acre|lk=out|abbr=on|sigfig=3}} and is named after the 1,187&nbsp;m tall [[Mudeungsan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=무등산국립공원 (Mudeungsan National Park)|url=http://terms.naver.com/entry.nhn?docId=1094682&cid=40942&categoryId=35591|publisher=두산백과 ([[Doosan Encyclopedia]])|language=Korean|access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref>

