'''Veronica Della Dora''' {{postnominal-GBR|FBA}} (born 1976) is Professor of Human Geography and Director of the Social, Cultural & Historical Geography Group at [[Royal Holloway, University of London]].<ref name="rh-profile">{{cite web |title=Professor Veronica Della Dora |url=https://pure.royalholloway.ac.uk/portal/en/persons/veronica-della-dora(f71cf662-e123-4000-a72b-e186eb1037c2).html |website=Geography: Researchers |publisher=Royal Holloway, University of London |accessdate=2 September 2018}}</ref>
She comes from [[Venice]] and grew up living on the [[Lido di Venezia|Lido]].<ref name=runciman />. She gained a PhD from [[University of California, Los Angeles]] in 2005; her thesis title was "Geographies of the holy mountain : post-Byzantine and western representations of the Monastic Republic of Mount Athos".<ref name="worldcat-thesis">{{cite web |title=Catalogue record for thesis |url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/geographies-of-the-holy-mountain-post-byzantine-and-western-representations-of-the-monastic-republic-of-mount-athos/oclc/62460898&referer=brief_results |publisher=Worldcat |accessdate=2 September 2018}}</ref>
Her book ''Landscape, Nature and the Sacred in Byzantium'' was nominated for the 2017 [[Runciman Award]].<ref name="runciman">{{cite web |title=An interview with Veronica della Dora, author of Landscape, Nature and the Sacred in Byzantium |url=https://runcimanaward.wixsite.com/authorinterviews/single-post/2017/06/07/An-interview-with-Veronica-della-Dora-author-of-Landscape-Nature-and-the-Sacred-in-Byzantium |publisher=Runciman Awards |accessdate=2 September 2018 |date=2017}}</ref>
In 2018 she was elected a [[Fellow of the British Academy]].<ref name="ba-profile">{{cite web |title=Professor Veronica Della Dora |url=https://www.britac.ac.uk/users/professor-veronica-della-dora |publisher=[[British Academy]] |accessdate=2 September 2018}}</ref>
==Selected publications== *''High Places: Cultural Geographies of Mountains and Ice'' (2008, [[Denis Cosgrove|Cosgrove, D]] and Della Dora, V.; I.B. Tauris: {{ISBN|9781845116170}}) *''Visual and Historical Geographies: Essays in Honour of Denis E. Cosgrove'' (2010, edited by Della Dora, V; Digby, S; Basdas, B.; Royal Geographical Society - Institute of British Geographers, 2010: {{ISBN|9781870074247}}) *''Imagining Mount Athos: Visions of a Holy Place from Homer to World War II'' (2011, University of Virginia Press: {{ISBN|978-0-8139-3259-0}}) *''Christian Pilgrimage, Landscape, and Heritage: Journeying to the Sacred'' (2014, Maddrell, Avril ; Della Dora, Veronica; Scafi, Alessandro; Walton, Heather; Routledge: {{ISBN|978-0-415-84398-0}}) *''Mountain: Nature and Culture'' (2016, Reaktion Books: {{ISBN|9781780236476}}) *''Landscape, Nature, and the Sacred in Byzantium'' (2016, Cambridge University Press: {{ISBN|9781107139091 }})
